egulated sex between men, the rise of male prostitution, and the aesthetics of male beauty. Drawing on this trove of material, Vitiello presents a historical outline of changing notions of male homosexuality in China, revealing the integral part that same-sex desire has played in its culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aGaysxChina. 0aGayszChina. 0aHomosexualityxChina. 0aHomosexualityzChina. 0aSex customsxChina. 0aSex customszChina. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226857954423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226857954.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles